<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_bæzn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bæzn</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bæzdæ</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>толщина</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>thickness</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>густота</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>density</q></cit></sense></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Отвлеченное от <xr><ref target="#entry_bæz-"/></xr> ‘толстый’, образованное суффиксом -%in%i (← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>-na</w></mentioned>), как <xr><ref target="#entry_bærn"/></xr> ‘ответственность’ от <xr><ref target="#entry_bar"/></xr>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>hvarnah-</w></mentioned> (ос. <xr><ref target="#entry_farn"/></xr>) от <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>hvar-</w></mentioned> и т. п. В <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><w>bæzdæ</w></mentioned> %id%i возникло, вероятно, перебойно из %in%i (*%ibæznæ%i → %ibæzdæ%i), ср. аналогичный перебой в <xr><ref target="#entry_qæznyg"/></xr> || qæzdyg ‘богатый’, <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><w>ǧæzdæ</w><gloss><q>богатство</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>32, 33, 37</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_РОСл."/><biblScope>596</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">An abstract word derived from <xr><ref target="#entry_bæz-"/></xr> ‘thick’ with the suffix -%in%i (← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>-na</w></mentioned>), like <xr><ref target="#entry_bærn"/></xr> ‘responsibility’ from <xr><ref target="#entry_bar"/></xr>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>hvarnah-</w></mentioned> (Ossetic <xr><ref target="#entry_farn"/></xr>) from <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>hvar-</w></mentioned> and so on. In <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><w>bæzdæ</w></mentioned> %id%i appeared probably from the transition of %in%i (*%ibæznæ%i → %ibæzdæ%i), cf. an similar transition in <xr><ref target="#entry_qæznyg"/></xr> || %iqæzdyg%i ‘rich’, <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><w>ǧæzdæ</w><gloss><q>wealth</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>32, 33, 37</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_РОСл."/><biblScope>596</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>